    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-21T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-21T06:00:00-05:00" n="711"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11564.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Canada</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-21T06:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1914, 6 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have you any further information confirming report that local authorities intend
                    to withdraw soldiers to Mexico City and tear up tracks? Keep O’Shaughnessy
                    informed and make every necessary arrangement for escape of foreigners in City
                    of Mexico. If any attempt is made to tear up track or otherwise embarrass or
                    hinder those who desire to leave Mexico, confer with Fletcher at once and join
                    him in vigorous protest against interruption of communication, keep us advised
                    promptly of any change in the situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
